    "cluster_id": "C008",
    "title": "saveState leaves orphan tmp files on any failure after writeFile — wx flag amplifies the problem",
    "file": "mcp/server/src/state.ts",
    "line_ranges": [
      "138-156"
    ],
    "agreement_count": 1,
    "reviewers": [
      3
    ],
    "max_severity": "medium",
    "min_severity": "medium",
    "disputed_severity": false,
    "categories": [
      "error-handling"
    ],
    "recommendations": [
      "Wrap the open→sync→close→rename block in try/catch that unlinks the tmp file in the catch (best-effort, swallowing only ENOENT). Alternatively, document the expected cleanup behavior and add a startup sweep that removes stale `state.tmp-*` files older than a few minutes. The 'wx' guarantee that the file did not pre-exist needs a counterpart 'we always clean up after ourselves' guarantee."
    ],
    "descriptions": [
      "saveState writes to `state.tmp-${Date.now()}-${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2)}.json` with `{ flag: 'wx' }`, then opens, syncs, closes, and renames. If anything between writeFile-success and rename throws (open rejects, sync rejects, close rejects, rename rejects with EBUSY/EACCES), the tmp file is left behind — there is no try/catch wrapping the durability sequence to unlink the tmp on failure. Combined with cycle 2's archive directory lifecycle, the user's `.sui-deepbook-course/` directory accumulates `state.tmp-*.json` files. Worse, a Math.random() suffix collision with a leftover tmp from a prior crashed run means the subsequent writeFile gets EEXIST and `saveState` permanently rejects — the contract surfaces it (good) but the recovery path requires the user to manually inspect and delete `.sui-deepbook-course/state.tmp-*.json`."
    ],
    "impacts": [
      "Disk litter under normal operation; permanent saveState failure under collision (rare but real because Math.random() entropy is short and the user might run many save cycles). Cycle 2 carry-forward C016 was supposed to harden the durability path; the wx hardening introduces a new fallback hazard that wasn't present pre-cycle-3."
    ],
    "evidence": "await fsPromises.writeFile(tmpPath, bytes, { flag: 'wx', mode: 0o600 });",
    "confidence_spread": [
      "high"
    ],
    "source_ids": [
      "R3-003"
    ]
  },
