    ],
    "descriptions": [
      "saveState's durability sequence first calls handle.sync() (the A18-prescribed FileHandle.sync) and then immediately calls fs.fsyncSync(handle.fd) on the same descriptor. The inline comment admits the second call is 'Redundant but required for T-061's fs.fsync* spy ordering assertion.' Production code is doing the same syscall twice solely so a leftover cycle-2 test ordering spy still fires."
    ],
    "impacts": [
      "An extra fsync on every saveState write (cheap, but real I/O) and, more importantly, a load-bearing piece of production code whose only purpose is to keep a test happy. Future maintainers will see two fsyncs and reasonably wonder if removing one breaks durability — they have to dig into a defunct cycle-2 spy to understand."
    ],
    "evidence": "await handle.sync();\n      // Redundant but required for T-061's fs.fsync* spy ordering assertion.\n      fs.fsyncSync(handle.fd);",
    "confidence_spread": [
      "high"
    ],
