      "Use action.timeoutMs ?? DEPLOY_TIMEOUT_MS in the setTimeout call so the action object remains the single source of truth for the executor's timeout.",
      "After SIGTERM, schedule a follow-up SIGKILL (e.g. setTimeout(() => child.kill('SIGKILL'), 10000)) so a wedged child is forcibly reaped. Alternatively, race the close event against a hard deadline and resolve the promise even if close never fires (the os will eventually reap the child)."
    ],
    "descriptions": [
      "runRealDeploy enforces the hard timeout via a setTimeout that uses the module-level DEPLOY_TIMEOUT_MS constant (420000). The action object passed in carries its own action.timeoutMs (which the manifest probe sets to 420000 on the fail path), but runRealDeploy never reads action.timeoutMs. If a future caller ever attaches a different timeoutMs to the shell action, the executor will silently use the module constant.",
      "On the 7-minute timeout, runRealDeploy calls `child.kill()` which sends SIGTERM (Node's default). If the spawned `pnpm deploy-all --quick` ignores SIGTERM (e.g. a wrapper script that traps it, or a deeply-nested docker-compose subprocess that needs to drain), the `close` event never fires and the returned promise never settles. The contract calls this a 'hard timeout' but the implementation only enforces a soft TERM-and-hope."
    ],
    "impacts": [
      "Today both values equal 420000 so the bug is dormant. Any future drift between the manifest probe's emitted action.timeoutMs and the executor's constant becomes invisible — the user-facing 'timeoutMs: ...' that runPreflightProbe surfaces in its response could disagree with what the executor actually enforces.",
      "Under realistic deploy-all conditions on a slow CI host or a wedged Docker daemon, the MCP tool call could hang indefinitely past the 7-minute budget. T-145 doesn't catch this because makeFakeChild's kill() emits close synchronously. Phase F's real T-157 exercise is where this would surface — and the synthesis-notes already flagged Phase F as the gating scenario."
    ],
    "evidence": "const timeoutHandle = setTimeout(() => {\n      timedOut = true;\n      child.kill();\n    }, DEPLOY_TIMEOUT_MS);",
    "confidence_spread": [
      "high",
      "medium"
    ],
    "source_ids": [
      "R1-001",
      "R1-005"
    ]
  },
