      "Push the remediation executor into the probe interface itself: extend `ProbeFn` (or add a sibling `RemediationFn`) so each probe optionally exposes `remediate(action) => Promise<RemediationResult>`. The tool handler becomes: `if (remediate && result.action) return probe.remediate(result.action)`. Probes without a remediation simply don't expose the function. The handler is then truly probe-agnostic. (Smaller alternative: keep the current shape but add a comment in runPreflightProbe.ts explicitly acknowledging that today only manifest has remediation, and that the hard-coded import is deliberate-for-now.)"
