    ],
    "descriptions": [
      "preflight.ts maintains a module-level mutable Map of spawn overrides keyed by probe id, and exports a public function setSpawnOverride that any caller in the same import graph can use to swap the spawn implementation of any probe at runtime. This is a test-only seam (used by scripts/e2e/harness.ts withDockerStub / withSuiCliStub fixtures) but it is not gated behind NODE_ENV, a test-only build, or a private symbol — it is part of the production export surface the MCP server ships.",
      "runProbe does PROBE_REGISTRY[probeId as ProbeId] with only a falsy guard (if (!probe)). Because PROBE_REGISTRY is a plain object literal, lookups for inherited keys like 'constructor' resolve to Object (truthy) and 'toString' resolves to Object.prototype.toString (truthy callable). The if (!probe) guard does not detect these. The tool layer (runPreflightProbe.ts line 25) does pre-validate with PROBE_ORDER.includes(probeId), so the MCP-facing surface is safe — but runProbe is exported and any in-process importer that bypasses the tool can reach this state."
    ],
    "impacts": [
      "No exploit path from the MCP boundary today: neither tool handler (start, runPreflightProbe) calls setSpawnOverride, and the registered Zod schemas don't accept an injectable spawn fn. Risk is forward-looking: any future tool, plugin, or third-party importer in the same runtime can poison probes #1/#3/#4 (the three spawn-driven probes) into reporting fake passes, undermining AC-2.4's hard-stop guarantee. Mirrors the synthesis-notes concern that workers must not leak test-API into production.",
      "Not exploitable across the MCP trust boundary today. Calling runProbe('constructor', {}) in-process invokes Object as a function, returning a wrapped opts object that flows to the caller as a malformed ProbeResult ({ pass: undefined, message: undefined, action: undefined }). Calling runProbe('toString', {}) succeeds and returns a string, which downstream would treat as a non-result. No authorization bypass, no shell action emission."
    ],
    "evidence": "const spawnOverrides = new Map<ProbeId, SpawnFn>();\n\nexport function setSpawnOverride(probeId: ProbeId, spawnFn: SpawnFn): () => void {\n  spawnOverrides.set(probeId, spawnFn);",
